pr_review_comment_body:
@graingert I've removed `pypy2.7-5.8.0` and left the more general `pypy`. 

Should `pypy3.5-5.9.0` also be excluded from `TOX_SUFFIX="flakes"`? Everything else but 3.6 is. 

`pypy` is also excluded from `TOX_SUFFIX="aiohttp"`. Should `pypy3.5-5.9.0` be excluded too?

@larroy I was talking about this code: https://github.com/apache/incubator-mxnet/blob/c4a76da62fbc5e3e7272fd89294fba6b22868bba/src/operator/c_lapack_api.h#L218

It seems like @lebeg and @larroy are both working on the USE_LAPACK flag. While this PR assumes the "wrong" behaviour of our build system to basically ignore the flag (as described in the ticket), https://github.com/apache/incubator-mxnet/pull/11094 attempts to correct this. I think we should first get https://github.com/apache/incubator-mxnet/pull/11094 merged properly. After that, we actually have a USE_LAPACK behaviour that behaves like expected. This would allows us to remove the hacks we have in this PR (USE_LAPACK=0) and thus reach a clean state.

If we merge this PR first and https://github.com/apache/incubator-mxnet/pull/11094 gets merged afterwards, the LAPACK build is broken again. I'd prefer a clean solution over multiple PRs about the same issue.

```go
if os.Getenv("GNUPGHOME") != "" {
        return os.Getenv("GNUPGHOME")
}
usr, err := user.Current()
if err != nil {
        return "~/.gnupg"
}
return path.Join(usr.HomeDir, ".gnupg")
```

